solution: SELECT t2.visitor_id ,  t1.name ,  t1.Level_of_membership FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id GROUP BY t2.visitor_id ORDER BY sum(t2.Total_spent) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.id, T1.name, T2.membership_level FROM visitor AS T1 INNER JOIN ticket AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.visitor_id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY SUM(T2.price) DESC LIMIT 1;

solution: SELECT t2.Museum_ID ,  t1.name FROM museum AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID GROUP BY t2.Museum_ID ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT id, name FROM museum WHERE visit_count = ( SELECT MAX(visit_count) FROM museum );

solution: SELECT name FROM museum WHERE Museum_ID NOT IN (SELECT museum_id FROM visit)
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM museum AS T1 JOIN visitor AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.museum_id WHERE T2.visitor_id IS NULL;

solution: SELECT t1.name ,  t1.age FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id ORDER BY t2.num_of_ticket DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.name, T2.age FROM Visitor AS T1 INNER JOIN Ticket AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.visitor_id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY COUNT(T2.id) DESC LIMIT 1;

solution: SELECT avg(num_of_ticket) ,  max(num_of_ticket) FROM visit
answer: SELECT AVG(Tickets), MAX(Tickets) FROM Visit

solution: SELECT sum(t2.Total_spent) FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id WHERE t1.Level_of_membership  =  1
answer: SELECT SUM(TotalExpense) FROM Tickets WHERE VisitorID IN (SELECT VisitorID FROM Visitors WHERE MembershipLevel = 1)

solution: SELECT t1.name FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id JOIN museum AS t3 ON t3.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t3.open_year  <  2009 INTERSECT SELECT t1.name FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id JOIN museum AS t3 ON t3.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t3.open_year  >  2011
answer: SELECT v.visitor FROM museum m JOIN visitor v ON m.id = v.museum_id WHERE m.opened_before = '2009' AND m.opened_after = '2011'

solution: SELECT count(*) FROM visitor WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT t2.visitor_id FROM museum AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t1.open_year  >  2010)
answer: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM visitors WHERE visit_id NOT IN ( SELECT visit_id FROM museum_visit WHERE museum_id IN ( SELECT museum_id FROM museum WHERE open_year > 2010 ) );

solution: SELECT count(*) FROM museum WHERE open_year  >  2013 OR open_year  <  2008
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.id) FROM museum AS T1 INNER JOIN opening_year AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.museum_id WHERE T2.opening_year > 2013 OR T2.opening_year < 2008;

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  GovernmentForm FROM country GROUP BY GovernmentForm HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  >  72
answer: SELECT T1.name, SUM(T2.population) FROM government_form AS T1 INNER JOIN life_expectancy AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.government_form_id WHERE T2.average_life_expectancy > 72 GROUP BY T1.name;

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  GovernmentForm FROM country GROUP BY GovernmentForm HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  >  72
answer: SELECT T1.name, AVG(T2.life_expectancy) FROM government_form AS T1 JOIN life_expectancy AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.government_form_id WHERE T2.life_expectancy > 72 GROUP BY T1.name;

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
answer: SELECT AVG(Life_Expectancy), SUM(Population) FROM Continent WHERE Life_Expectancy < 72 GROUP BY Continent;

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
answer: SELECT T2.continent, AVG(T1.life_expectancy) AS avg_life_expectancy, SUM(T1.population) AS total_population FROM life_expectancy AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.country_id = T2.id WHERE T2.continent IN ( SELECT continent FROM country GROUP BY continent HAVING AVG(life_expectancy) < 72 )

solution: SELECT Name ,  SurfaceArea FROM country ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 5
answer: SELECT T1.name, T2.area FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.country_id ORDER BY T2.area DESC LIMIT 5;

solution: SELECT Name ,  SurfaceArea FROM country ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 5
answer: SELECT T1.name, (T2.surface_area * 1000000) AS surface_area FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Continent AS T2 ON T1.continent_id = T2.id ORDER BY T2.population DESC LIMIT 5;

solution: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population DESC LIMIT 3
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Population AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.country_code ORDER BY T2.population DESC LIMIT 3;

solution: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population DESC LIMIT 3
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Region AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.code WHERE T2.population > 1000 ORDER BY T1.population DESC LIMIT 3;

solution: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population ASC LIMIT 3
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Population AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.code ORDER BY T2.population ASC LIMIT 3;

solution: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population ASC LIMIT 3
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Population AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.country_code ORDER BY T2.population ASC LIMIT 3;

solution: SELECT count(*) FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Asia"
answer: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM C WHERE continent = 'Asia';

solution: SELECT count(*) FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Asia"
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.name) FROM C AS T1 INNER JOIN REGIONS AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.country_id WHERE T2.region = 'Asia';

solution: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Europe" AND Population  =  "80000"
answer: SELECT T2.name FROM C AS T1 INNER JOIN Country AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.code WHERE T1.continent = 'Europe' AND T2.population = 80000;

solution: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Europe" AND Population  =  "80000"
answer: SELECT T2.name FROM C AS T1 INNER JOIN Country AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.code WHERE T1.population = 80000 AND T2.region = 'Europe'

solution: select sum(population) ,  avg(surfacearea) from country where continent  =  "north america" and surfacearea  >  3000
answer: SELECT SUM(T1.population), AVG(T2.area) FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Continent AS T2 ON T1.continent = T2.name WHERE T2.name = 'North America' AND T1.area > 3000;

solution: select sum(population) ,  avg(surfacearea) from country where continent  =  "north america" and surfacearea  >  3000
answer: SELECT SUM(T1.population), AVG(T2.surface_area) FROM Country AS T1 INNER JOIN Area AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.country_code WHERE T2.area >= 3000 AND T2.region = 'North America';

solution: SELECT name FROM city WHERE Population BETWEEN 160000 AND 900000
answer: SELECT city FROM cities WHERE population BETWEEN 160000 AND 900000;

solution: select name from city where population between 160000 and 900000
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM city AS T1 JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.id WHERE T1.population BETWEEN 160000 AND 900000;

solution: SELECT LANGUAGE FROM countrylanguage GROUP BY LANGUAGE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT LANGUAGE FROM countrylanguage GROUP BY LANGUAGE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT LANGUAGE ,  CountryCode ,  max(Percentage) FROM countrylanguage GROUP BY CountryCode
answer: SELECT T1.language, T2.country FROM language AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.id GROUP BY T2.country ORDER BY COUNT(T1.id) DESC LIMIT 3;

solution: SELECT T1.Name ,  sum(T2.Sales) FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name
answer: SELECT T1.name, SUM(T2.sales) FROM Singer AS T1 INNER JOIN Song AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.singer_id GROUP BY T1.name;

solution: SELECT T1.Name ,  sum(T2.Sales) FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name
answer: SELECT SUM(sales) FROM songs WHERE singer_id IN (SELECT id FROM singers);

solution: SELECT Name FROM singer WHERE Singer_ID NOT IN (SELECT Singer_ID FROM song)
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.singer_id WHERE T2.id IS NULL;

solution: SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  <  1945 INTERSECT SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  >  1955
answer: SELECT DISTINCT citizenship FROM singer WHERE birth_year BETWEEN 1945 AND 1955;

solution: SELECT count(*) FROM Other_Available_Features
answer: SELECT COUNT(T1.feature_id) FROM feature AS T1 INNER JOIN variant AS T2 ON T1.feature_id = T2.feature_id WHERE T2.variant_char = 'A' AND T2.variant_num = 80;

solution: SELECT T2.feature_type_name FROM Other_Available_Features AS T1 JOIN Ref_Feature_Types AS T2 ON T1.feature_type_code  =  T2.feature_type_code WHERE T1.feature_name  =  "AirCon"
answer: SELECT T2.feature_type_name FROM features AS T1 INNER JOIN feature_types AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.id WHERE T1.name = 'AirCon';

solution: SELECT T2.property_type_description FROM Properties AS T1 JOIN Ref_Property_Types AS T2 ON T1.property_type_code  =  T2.property_type_code GROUP BY T1.property_type_code
answer: SELECT property_type_description FROM properties WHERE code IN (SELECT code FROM properties WHERE property_type_description IS NOT NULL)

solution: SELECT property_name FROM Properties WHERE property_type_code  =  "House" UNION SELECT property_name FROM Properties WHERE property_type_code  =  "Apartment" AND room_count  >  1
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM properties AS T1 INNER JOIN houses AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.property_id INNER JOIN apartments AS T3 ON T1.id = T3.property_id WHERE T2.rooms > 1 OR T3.rooms > 1
